It looks like winter will be good for German tourism entrepreneurs:
According to one study, there was a significant increase in bookings for the coming months compared with the previous year - even more than 30 percent for the winter season.
Despite weak economic growth, the German appetite for travel remains intact.
For the winter season, travel agencies recorded a 31 percent increase in turnover compared with the same period last year, the German Travel Association (Deutscher Reiseverband, DRV) reported in Berlin on Monday.
