Re-establish the republic around 21st century socialism.
This is a joint project of Hugo Chávez, a Venezuelan, Eva Morales, a Bolivian, and Rafael Correy, an Ecuadorian.
Last Sunday, the third nominee put to a vote, following the example of his counterparts and friends, a draft of a new constitution.
And his mission is accomplished, as 64% of the voters, according to official results covering 80% of the vote, voted "yes" in the referendum.
