To pass the Constitution, he had to get half the vote plus one.
Two polls at the exit of the polling stations and a poll by an NGO predicted a clear "yes" victory on Sunday, putting it between 63% and 70%.
Rafael Correa, by the way, demanded the victory of his constitution on the night of Sunday to Monday.
