The situation in Afghanistan and Pakistan, and terrorism in all its forms, were condemned by both sides and called for an urgent UN conference.
They also urged the conclusion of the Doha round of trade talks, although both have a large share in its failure so far.
The European Union has confirmed that it will stick to its energy and climate agenda, which is to reduce emissions by at least 20% by 2020.
India has agreed to this, as well as the need to reach a global agreement at next year's climate conference to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 50 percent by 2050.
Both sides would also like to prevent food price increases and support the convening of an international conference to discuss the financial crisis.
